Incidentally I started building a new updater yesterday. The first test script identifies a certain method in both old and new engine clients with only one false positive when I ran it against a non-zkmstripped old engine client in high-tolerance mode (it still found the correct method though and it was extremely obvious which one it was). Completely regex-free at the moment, but I think I might incorporate them as a secondary line of false-positive checking.
